قالَ ٯل
qāf ’alqi-hā has been provided with one single diacritical stroke placed above and probably added by a later hand, as in all the manuscript the copyist has the habit not to provide qāf with diacritics. As qāf was distinguished by a dot above or below in the second century H, the addition of the diacritic in the ms could suggest the period in which the later hand has worked. However the system of distinguishing qāf placing a dot above and fā’ with a dot below has been preserved in maghribi script so that the position of the diacritic in the ms could suggest the provenance of the later hand الڧها ىمو
